(firstQuint)Plasma Transfusion in Liver Transplantation.

 Three types of plasma are transfused in bleeding patients undergoing liver transplantation: - quarantined plasma, - methylene blue treated plasma, - solvent/detergent plasma.

 The main purpose is to show that the volume of methylene blue treated plasma consumed intraoperatively is equivalent to that of the 2 other types of plasma.

 In addition, the correction of coagulation abnormalities are studied.

